40|$|<b>Road</b> <b>users</b> not {{abiding by}} {{the rule of}} tram {{priority}} has {{increased the number of}} crashes between trams and other <b>road</b> <b>users.</b> This study focuses on the perceptions of pedestrians, cyclists, and motorists regarding the risk of crashes with trams. The first aim was to examine how these <b>road</b> <b>users</b> assess the risk of tram crashes with themselves and with other <b>road</b> <b>users</b> of the same age and type. The second aim was to look into whether and to what extent road users' comparative judgments about tram risk are realistic in terms of their self-reported behaviour...|$|R
